quran[51]{c,v,t}:
  26,1,"Ta, Seen, Meem"
  26,2,These are the signs of the Manifest Book
  26,3,"You are liable to imperil your life [out of distress] that they will not have faith"
  26,4,If We wish We will send down to them a sign from the sky before which their heads will remain bowed in humility
  26,5,There does not come to them any new reminder from the All-beneficent but that they disregard it
  26,6,"They have already denied [the truth], but soon there will come to them the news of what they have been deriding"
  26,7,"Have they not regarded the earth, how many of every splendid kind [of vegetation] We have caused to grow in it"
  26,8,There is indeed a sign in that; but most of them do not have faith
  26,9,"Indeed your Lord is the All-mighty, the All-merciful"
  26,10,"When your Lord called out to Moses: [saying,] ‘Go to those wrongdoing people"
  26,11,"the people of Pharaoh. Will they not be wary [of Allah]?’"
  26,12,"He said, ‘My Lord! I fear they will impugn me"
  26,13,"and I will become upset and my tongue will fail me. So send for Aaron [to join me]"
  26,14,"Besides, they have a charge against me, and I fear they will kill me.’"
  26,15,"He said, ‘Certainly not! Let both of you go with Our signs: We will indeed be with you, hearing [everything]"
  26,16,"So approach Pharaoh and say, ‘‘We are indeed envoys of the Lord of the worlds"
  26,17,that you let the Children of Israel leave with us.’’ ’
  26,18,"He [i.e. Pharaoh] said, ‘Did we not rear you as a child among us, and did you not stay with us for years of your life"
  26,19,"Then you committed that deed of yours, and you are an ingrate.’"
  26,20,"He said, ‘I did that when I was astray"
  26,21,"So I fled from you, as I was afraid of you. Then my Lord gave me sound judgement and made me one of the apostles"
  26,22,That you have enslaved the Children of Israel—is that the favour with which you reproach me?’
  26,23,"He said, ‘And what is ‘‘the Lord of all the worlds?’’ ’"
  26,24,"He said, ‘The Lord of the heavens and the earth and whatever is between them,—should you have conviction.’"
  26,25,"He said to those who were around him, ‘Don’t you hear?!’"
  26,26,"He said, ‘Your Lord, and the Lord of your forefathers!’"
  26,27,"He said, ‘Indeed your messenger, who has been sent to you, is surely crazy!’"
  26,28,"He said, ‘The Lord of the east and the west and whatever is between them—should you exercise your reason.’"
  26,29,"He said, ‘If you take up any god other than me, I will surely make you a prisoner!’"
  26,30,"He said, ‘What if I bring you something [as an] unmistakable [proof]?’"
  26,31,"He said, ‘Then bring it, should you be truthful.’"
  26,32,"Thereat he threw down his staff, and behold, it was a manifest python"
  26,33,"Then he drew out his hand, and behold, it was white and bright to the onlookers"
  26,34,"He said to the elite [who stood] around him, ‘This is indeed an expert magician"
  26,35,who seeks to expel you from your land with his magic. So what do you advise?’
  26,36,"They said, ‘Put him and his brother off for a while, and send heralds to the cities"
  26,37,to bring you every expert magician.’
  26,38,So the magicians were gathered for the tryst of a known day
  26,39,"and the people were told: ‘Will you all gather?!’"
  26,40,"‘Maybe we will follow the magicians, if they are victors!’"
  26,41,"So when the magicians came, they said to Pharaoh, ‘Shall we have a reward if we were to be the victors?’"
  26,42,"He said, ‘Of course; and you will be among members of my inner circle.’"
  26,43,"Moses said to them, ‘Throw down whatever you have to throw!’"
  26,44,"So they threw down their sticks and ropes, and said, ‘By the might of Pharaoh, we shall surely be victorious!’"
  26,45,"Thereat Moses threw down his staff, and behold, it was swallowing what they had faked"
  26,46,Thereat the magicians fell down prostrating
  26,47,"They said, ‘We believe in the Lord of all the worlds"
  26,48,the Lord of Moses and Aaron.’
  26,49,"He [i.e. Pharaoh] said, ‘Do you profess faith in Him before I should permit you? He is indeed your chief who has taught you magic! Soon you will know! I will cut off your hands and feet from opposite sides, and I will crucify you all.’"
  26,50,"They said, ‘[There is] no harm [in that]! Indeed, we shall return to our Lord"
  26,51,Indeed we hope our Lord will forgive us our offences for being the first to believe.’